Simulation results at three representative latitudes (61°N, 71°N, and 81°N) for the historical period (1961–2005) and RCP8.5 scenario (2061–2100), showing sea-ice GPP under different levels of availability of dissolved silicate according to the calculated 10th, 50th, and 90th percentiles of measured winter silicates at a depth of 10 m between 1948 and 2000, retrieved from the Hydrochemical Atlas of the Arctic Ocean (
     
